title: Junior Programmer
description:
Join one of Southest Asia's largest specialised clinic groups 

Established in 2003, City Fertility is one of Australia's leading IVF and fertility services group with 10 IVF clinics, 70+ consulting rooms and 50+ fertility specialists nationwide.

City Fertility Career Opportunities: https://www.cityfertility.com.au/about-us/career-opportunities/ 

What we offer:

Competitive salary and compensation
	Ethical business model
	Extensive support networks
	Positive and safe workplace culture and environment
	Parental Leave and Fertility Benefits Program 
	Professional development and career development opportunities
	Access to an Employee Assistance Programs for physical, mental, social, family and financial support
All personal information received by CF will be stored, used and disclosed by us in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
About the Role

This is an excellent opportunity for a junior and innovative programmer to join us in permanent full-time basis in the corporate City Fertility head offices in Newstead.

About the business

Over 6,500 babies and countless smiles for more than 15 years.
Established in 2003, City Fertility (CFC) is one of Australia ’s leading IVF & fertility service groups.  We provide seamless care across the full fertility spectrum, while ensuring the best possible chances of conception for our patients through our rigorous protocols and actively taking part in research projects and science-based treatments.

CFC has recently joined the CHA IVF global network, which has a 35-year track record as world-renowned pioneers in reproductive medicine. This Partnership provides City Fertility with unique access to CHA and SMG’s globally renowned medical, operational, and research & development expertise.
Refer to our website www.cityfertility.com.au under the ABOUT tab for more information about City Fertility and our partnerships with CHA Medical Group.

What we offer:

• Ethical business model
• Positive and safe workplace culture and environment
• Great team and support networks
• Professional development and career development opportunities
• Ongoing career appraisals and recognition of career milestones achieved
• Access to an Employee Assistance Program

We are committed to the development of our people and invest in ongoing training to improve performance, provide career development opportunities and offer competitive salaries. City Fertility is an equal opportunity employer - All facets of diversity are important to us and we endeavour to create an environment where everyone, regardless of factors such as gender, age, ability, race, ethnicity, sexual orientation, gender identification or religion, can contribute to our progressive business.

The Opportunity
City Fertility are looking for a Junior Programmer who can assist in software projects. We are going through transformation from legacy to state-of-the-art systems and need someone who can work in team with other developers to write state-of-the-art code. 
Qualifications

BA/BS degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or related field, or equivalent practical experience
	Minimum 1 years’ experience in C#/.NET framework
	Front-end JavaScript frameworks
	Producing high-quality code utilising unit testing framework and code review practices
	Version control tools such as Git and TFS
	Good communication skills, written and verbal
	Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail
	Capacity to work in Australia
Desirables

Understanding of SQL is desirable but not essential i-e MSSQL queries, stored procs, functions, working with linked servers, etc
Valid Australian visa with work rights - You must be legally entitled to work in Australia to accept this position and will be required to show proof of employability with a copy of your Australian visa advising of visa details and entitlements or Australian birth certificate. An Australian visa check will be completed on all successful candidates.

Personal Attributes

Innovative and out-of-the-box thinker.
	Able to comfortably work to tight deadlines with little or no supervision.
	Mature attitude to developing communication with team members
	Ability to work to flexible timelines in order to meet deadlines.
	Able to grasp new technologies and keep up to date with changes.
Application process

If this is the job for you, then apply through our company website recruitment portal via:

www.cityfertility.com.au > Contact Us > Careers Page. 

Closing Date: 14/10/2022

All personal information received by will be stored, used and disclosed by us in accordance with our Privacy Policy.

title: Software Development Consultant - Graduate Program

title: Junior Full-Stack Engineer
description:
About your opportunity...
Flight Centre Travel Group is looking for a Junior Full-Stack Engineer who is as passionate about delivering innovative solutions to delight our customers. 
This is an exciting opportunity to build reliable, scalable solutions with a focus on delivering value to our customers. You will be working as part of a well-established team on our Omni Channel initiative. Our ideal applicant will be no stranger to working with agile software development, and has experience using appropriate agile methodologies and lean practices.
We value teamwork, and with us you will have the opportunity to work across multiple teams and contribute to our culture of engineering and operational excellence whilst also honing your skillet. 
Technology fly's fast! Our people use their quick thinking expertise, and tenacity to figure things out and keep us moving forward. Our people are as agile as the solutions we put in place - if this sounds like you, APPLY NOW.
 
What You’ll Do...

Design, build efficient, testable, and maintainable code with the right balance between solving the problem at hand and not over-engineering your solution
Work across the entire end to end stack, front-end web applications using modern JavaScript libraries such as React, and backend microservices/APIs using Node.js and Java
Collaborate in our cross-functional Product Management and Engineering teams to plan and deliver high quality solutions in a fast-paced, agile environment
Take initiative and always look for ways in improving the quality of our solutions, code bases, technical debt, standards, processes, and best practices

 
Who you are...

Experience in software development, using modern JavaScript coding, testing and automation techniques to deliver end-to-end solutions
Experience in building user-friendly, responsive web applications for desktop and mobile
Experience in some of the following: TypeScript, React, CSS (JSS), Cypress and Jest
Passionate about software engineering best practices and know what it means to ship high-quality code that is maintainable and extendable
Highly collaborative team-player who thrives in a team environment without being adversarial and can also work independently
You have a growth mindset, embracing challenges to continuously improve and innovate

 
What’s in it for you...

Generous remuneration structure & Employee Share Scheme
Travel & Accommodation discounts, in-house financial & health services, access to internal 24/7 gym & End-of-Trip Facility
Ongoing training & professional development
Flexible working environment, with WFH options available
Brightness Of Future: Employees have the right to see a clear pathway to achieving career ambitions, and promotion and transfers from within are our preference
Global career opportunities in a network of brands and businesses
Proud Corporate Social Responsibility platform through the Flight Centre Foundation, Responsible Travel Charter, and Brighter Futures programs
Potential to attend Global Award Events (Global Gathering Bali 2023)

 
Who we are...
At Flight Centre Travel Group, our vision is to open up the world for those who want to see.
As a global travel retailer, our people come from all different backgrounds, and our connections spread to the far reaches of the globe. Together, we are a family.
We offer genuine opportunities for people to grow and evolve. We embrace new experiences, seize all opportunities, and empower all our people to find their Brightness of Future.
We DREAM BIG through collaboration and innovation and are supported to make incredible ideas a reality. We deliver quality, innovative digital solutions to delight our customers and achieve our strategic priorities.
Irreverence. Ownership. Egalitarianism.

As a result, this opening is purely based on growth with no plans on slowing.    The team genuinely care about your level of passion working on a particular platform and will check-in on a monthly basis to ensure you are satisfied with the work you are doing. Not satisfied? The team will make their best efforts to provide you with new challenges/platform to work with to ensure you are getting the most out of your professional life.     They boast a flexible WFH policy and mainly attempt to all group together once a week in their inner city Brisbane office to host a team lunch/whiteboard session for new innovations as well as host discussions about potentially better ways their tech can be delivered!    Overall, the team has a great structure to up-skill, nurture, and provide opportunities for growth across your career.     The Stack:  Ideally 2 years+ experience with React.js and/or Vue.js. Node.js is used for the BE so any understanding/experience is highly desirable.  Any experience with Python or Golang is also a bonus (but now were are getting into Unicorn territory!)  If you have a passion for front-end development, a desire to join a supportive team, and are looking for an opportunity for growth in your career, I encourage you to apply or contact me directly!    More than happy to share full details of the role, company, and product roadmap upon consideration of individual applications.    Aaron Mancy Software Development | Just Digital People 0435 416 770 | aaron@justdigitalpeople.com.au

title: Junior Technical Analyst
description: Are you a mid-year finisher looking to launch your career in tech? The FDM Graduate Career Program can help you fast-track your dream career. Our long relationships with FTSE100 client partners allow a foot in the door that can be out of reach to many graduates, giving you the opportunity to add big brands on your CV. Grab this amazing opportunity to work with industry-leading companies including the top 4 banks, consultancies, insurance companies, retailers, and charities in Australia.A career where you are encouraged to meet your potentialWe are currently seeking candidates interested in building a career as a Technical Analyst – all degrees welcome. We have training start dates happening in June, July and August and throughout the year. If you're looking to start your career in technology, we want to hear from you now!About This RoleAlthough no prior technical experience is required, this is a role for a logical problem solver with a keen interest in technology. You ideally enjoy working with numbers, are a great team communicator and determined to succeed.Your reward will be an exciting and challenging role offering unlimited prospects for career growth and development. As a Technical Analyst, you will have the opportunity to apply your skills to innovative projects and make a real impact in a variety of sectors. You will be responsible for investigating and developing solutions for applications. It could be robotic process automation, quality assurance and IT infrastructure delivery for global businesses.The FDM Technical Analysis training program is designed to equip you with the skills and knowledge you need to start and grow a successful career. The 10-week industry specific training covers high demand skills such as SQL, Unix; Excel/VBA, BA, Python, ITIL, Cloud and OS-Admin.You’ll then set out on your career journey as an FDM consultant by working for one of our globally recognised clients. Junior Technical Analyst roles often involve high-profile projects in major financial institutions, working on sensitive information and gaining first-hand exposure to business operations. These opportunities are perfect for those who are team players with strong analytical skills and an aptitude for fast learning.About FDMFDM is a FTSE 250 employer operating across Asia-Pacific, the UK, mainland Europe and North America. Over a 30+ year history, FDM Group has won many awards. In 2022 FDM has risen 5 places to #16 on the GradConnection Top 100 Graduate Employers and is again one of GradAustralia's Top 100 Graduate Employers. In 2021 alone, we launched the careers of over 2,600 graduates globally. And we provide a wide range of opportunities for our consultants to work in technical roles alongside some of the world’s biggest brands.What will my time at FDM be like?Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s award-winning academy. While interviews and assessments are done remotely, you now have the option to undertake training online or at our centrally located 21st floor Sydney office in Barangaroo.You will receive the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout. After successfully completing your training, you’ll have the technical and professional skills you need to step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia during the two-year program.What we offer youCompetitive salary package and benefitsFully funded, industry-recognised training and qualificationsKey employability skills development - including Microsoft Excel, CV writing, interview and presentation techniquesA foot in the door to some of the world’s most reputable organisationsMentoring and ongoing support throughout your entire FDM journeyOption to do training in 21st floor Sydney office at prime Barangaroo location Social events and networking opportunities What will I offer FDM?Bachelor’s degree or higher, STEM major not requiredAn analytical, problem-solving mindset and passion to work within the IT industry with the ambition to succeedExcellent communication skills and eagerness to build relationshipsAbility to commit to completing our full 2.5-year graduate program – whether eligible under a single visa or as an Australian citizen/permanent residentGeographic flexibility throughout Sydney and Melbourne to support our top-tier clients Our cultureFDM is a company committed to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate difference because we want everyone to have equal opportunity to belong and grow in their career. We are active in creating a more gender-balanced workforce, with circa 33% of our senior management team and 31% of all employees identifying as female.Give yourself a head start – seize this opportunityThe industry demand for tech talent is so hot, there has never been a better time to launch an exciting IT career. Remember, you don’t need to have studied a STEM subject, what matters is your passion and drive.Apply now and give yourself the competitive advantage! The FDM Recruitment team will take you through the process and guide you to the path of your successful tech career.  FDM embraces diversity and encourages applications from people with disability. Candidates will have the opportunity to request support or reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process in order to demonstrate their ability to meet the inherent requirements of the job.

title: Junior Intergration Engineer
description: M2i Electrical Services is an engineering business based in Murarrie, Brisbane.  M2i services marine and industrial clients throughout Australia and overseas and offer design, programming, manufacture, installation and commissioning services. We service clients in the superyacht and commercial marine industry across Australia, South East Asia and Europe.  We are seeking a Junior Integration Engineer to join our team on projects in Australia and abroad.Key ResponsibilitiesSupport engineering team and installation staff on multiple and varied projectsNetwork configuration and troubleshooting in the marine environmentNetwork configuration and troubleshooting in the industrial environmentSupport internal and external stakeholders completing network installation and fault finding The successful candidate will possess the following skills and experience: Undergraduate or Postgraduate Computer Science, Engineering (Software/Electrical/Mechatronics)Proficient use of Microsoft Word & Excel for system documentation Microsoft Windows Configuration and troubleshootingNetwork Setup and ConfigurationSimple IPv4 Network addressing and troubleshootingMinimum 2 years programing / scripting experience in any of the following; Python, C/C++, PHP, VB, Java, JavaScript, Pascal, Embedded Systems, Linux,Bash, PowerShell, etc.API InterfacingDesirable ExperiencePLC ProgramingLadder logic, Functional Block Diagrams, Structured TextMicrocontroller PrototypingArduino, Raspberry Pi / Pico etcProcedural & Objective programing methodsCAD ExperienceAutoCAD Electrical, Altium, Eagle etc.Data / System SecurityAV & Control systemsFamiliarization with AV standards and automation systemsHDMI, HDBT, DANTECRESTRON, AMX, SAVANT, RTI, CONTROL 4Instrumentation interfacing and protocolsRS458, RS232, Modbus, Analogue Signals (4-20, 0-10v), MQTT, OPCUA A full-time permanent role with the opportunity to join a privately owned business that highly value their employees, with an opportunity for both interstate and international travel. Full time, part-time and flexible working arrangements are available, depending on individual circumstances. The remuneration package will be discussed at the interview stage.

title: Graduate Podiatrist for Mentorship Program
description: Are you a graduate podiatrist looking for the perfect fit? Don’t miss out on this mentorship opportunity in Brisbane, Queensland. Advance Foot Clinic, a leading podiatry business with five clinics in and around Brisbane’s Northern and Western suburbs, is seeking a full-time graduate. What will the mentorship program look like?For our new graduates, Advance Foot Clinic provides comprehensive training and one-on-one mentoring. You will have a dedicated mentor that will provide support and guidance as you learn and enhance your skills as a podiatrist. We will ensure you are exposed to a range of podiatric complaints and that you are given the opportunity to explore and grow in your career. What’s in it for you?A wide variety of interesting podiatry cases, such as sports and biomechanics, surgery, diabetic care, paediatric care, NDIS, DVA, occupational and rehabilitation podiatry, general foot care and home visits.Excellent working conditions and a flexible roster.Access to leading 3D laser scanning technology for the manufacture of orthotics and AFOs.Utilise the latest treatment technology such as microwave therapy for skin lesions & cold laser clinical machinery for onychomycosis.Extensive support from the entire team utilising the cloud-based practice management software - PracSuite.Opportunities for career development in an environment that encourages and enables constant learning, growth and development.An attractive remuneration package to match your experience and qualifications.Reimbursement for AHPRA registration fees and professional indemnity insurance.A fuel and phone allowance and continuing education allowance.Good coffee, lasting friendships and a comradery no one can match. What will you do?The role will focus on providing a premium client experience to each individual patient, while growing and maintaining a loyal client base. You will need to take initiative, demonstrate excellent communication skills and work cohesively with the podiatry and administration teams to enhance outcomes and achieve business objectives. Your dedicated mentor will help you to understand and reach these goals.Be exposed to all areas of podiatryBe part of a supportive and dedicated team with excellent working conditionsEnjoy autonomy in a diverse role with a flexible rosterHave full administrative support and career development opportunitiesAdvance Foot Clinic will mentor you closely to ensure you continue to grow and learn. We focus on bringing out the best in our team members, because we know this will result in the best experience for our patients. What do you need?Relevant Podiatry qualification and intention to register as a Podiatrist as soon as possible.Love people and enjoy adding value to their lives.Be confident, driven and motivated.Have an interest in all aspects of podiatry and a thirst for learning and growth.Thrive in a fast-paced work environment and be able to multitask.Be able to work independently, but also willing to follow direction and take constructive feedback.Have great integrity and a good sense of humour. Brisbane Clinic locations: Arana HillsBellbowrieChermsideAshgroveThe Gap Advance Foot Clinic is an all-encompassing podiatry practice with clinics across various locations on the Brisbane Northside. We pride ourselves on the fact that we do more than just look after people’s feet; we look after their health and well-being. Apply now by emailing your resume and a cover letter which highlights your suitability for the role to careers@afootc.com.au with the subject “I want to be part of the team!”.
